The paper proposes a new approach for contextual outlier detection, which is a fundamental data science task with applications in various fields such as data cleaning and network security. The approach utilizes a local and global behavioral model based on relevant contexts and presents several optimizations to improve scalability. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
